import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.barplot(x='group', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people across the groups?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('person').count().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='person', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max count: {data['count'].max():.2f}")
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('Which person appears in the most number of groups?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = data['count'].astype(int)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', bins=3, kde=False)
    plt.axvline(x=data['count'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['count'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of people in each group?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', bins=range(1, 4), color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["count"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group').size().reset_index(name='count')
    sns.barplot(x='group', y='count', data=group_sizes)
    plt.title('What is the most common group size?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
